Package: kmod-ipt-cluster
Version: 6.12-rc4-r1
Depends: kernel (=6.12-rc4~fff3398c9630f880d25c4265c32e159e-r1), kmod-ipt-core, kmod-nf-conntrack
Source: feeds/base/kernel/linux
SourceName: kernel
License: GPL-2.0-only
LicenseFiles: COPYING
Section: kernel
SourceDateEpoch: 1729793847
Architecture: x86_64
Installed-Size: 20480
Filename: kmod-ipt-cluster_6.12-rc4-r1_x86_64.ipk
Size: 3691
SHA256sum: 8c70a924c4f9fe5db06f6856cfd8ced7cc3f9f86e7acbde94c867da5dc2f7c7c
Description:  Netfilter (IPv4/IPv6) module for matching cluster
 This option allows you to build work-load-sharing clusters of
 network servers/stateful firewalls without having a dedicated
 load-balancing router/server/switch. Basically, this match returns
 true when the packet must be handled by this cluster node. Thus,
 all nodes see all packets and this match decides which node handles
 what packets. The work-load sharing algorithm is based on source
 address hashing.
 
 This module is usable for ipv4 and ipv6.
 
 To use it also enable iptables-mod-cluster
 
 see `iptables -m cluster --help` for more information.

